{"title_page": "Kartik Aaryan", "text_new": "{{pp-vandalism|small=yes}}\n{{Good article}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Kartik Aaryan\n| image        = Kartik Aaryan unveils the November issue of Filmfare.jpg\n| caption      = Aaryan at an event for ''[[Filmfare]]'' in 2019\n| birth_name   = Kartik Tiwari\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1990|11|22|df=yes}}<!-- DO NOT CHANGE! This has been verified by a high-quality reliable source-->\n| birth_place  = [[Gwalior]], [[Madhya Pradesh]], India\n| education    = D Y Patil College of Engineering, [[Navi Mumbai]]\n| occupation   = Actor\n| yearsactive  = 2011{{ndash}}present\n}}\n'''Kartik Tiwari''' (born 22 November 1990<!-- DO NOT CHANGE! This has been verified by a high-quality reliable source-->), known professionally as '''Kartik Aaryan''', is an Indian actor who appears in [[Bollywood|Hindi films]]. While pursuing an engineering degree in biotechnology, he dabbled in modelling and made attempts to start a career in film. After struggling for three years, Aaryan made his acting debut in 2011 with ''[[Pyaar Ka Punchnama]]'', a [[buddy film]] about the romantic tribulations faced by three young men, which was directed by [[Luv Ranjan]] and co-starred [[Nushrat Bharucha]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bloggerwlogger.com/.ShubhamSrivastava/Everything-that-you-should-know-if-you-are-a-Kartik-Aaryan-Fan-pfu77lyq1k4o/|title=Everything that you should know if you are a Kartik Aaryan Fan|website=bloggerwlogger.com|access-date=2020-04-24}}</ref>\n\nAaryan went on to play the romantic interest of the lead female characters in ''[[Akaash Vani]]'' (2013) and ''[[Kaanchi: The Unbreakable]]'' (2014), but these films failed to propel his career forward. He subsequently collaborated with Ranjan and Bharucha in two more buddy films, ''[[Pyaar Ka Punchnama 2]]'' (2015) and ''[[Sonu Ke Titu Ki Sweety]]'' (2018), both of which were commercially successful but received criticism for their misogynistic themes. The latter proved to be a breakthrough for Aaryan, and he followed it by starring in the 2019 romantic comedies ''[[Luka Chuppi]]'' and ''[[Pati Patni Aur Woh (2019 film)|Pati Patni Aur Woh]]''.\n\nIn addition to his acting career, Aaryan endorses several brands and products, and has co-hosted two award ceremonies. He appeared in ''[[Forbes India]]''{{'s}} [[Forbes Celebrity 100|Celebrity 100]] list of 2019.\n\n== Life and career ==\n\n=== Early life and work (1990\u20132017) ===\n\nKartik Tiwari (later Aaryan){{efn|name=A}} was born on 22 November 1990<!-- DO NOT CHANGE! This has been verified by a high-quality reliable source--> in [[Gwalior]], [[Madhya Pradesh]].<ref name=birthday>{{cite web|last=Hegde|first=Rajul|title=A happy woman is a myth, says Pyaar Ka Punchanama's Kartik Aaryan|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/a-happy-woman-is-a-myth-says-pyaar-ka-punchanamas-kartik-aryan-video/20151122.htm|publisher=[[Rediff.com]]|accessdate=13 April 2016|date=22 November 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160416021249/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/a-happy-woman-is-a-myth-says-pyaar-ka-punchanamas-kartik-aryan-video/20151122.htm|archivedate=16 April 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"chip\">{{cite news|last=Malik|first=Ektaa|title=Kartik Aaryan: New Chip of the Old Block|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/bollywood-kartik-aaryan-sony-titu-sweety-new-chip-of-the-old-block-5133639/|work=[[The Indian Express]]|accessdate=2 July 2018|date=12 April 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180425214630/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/bollywood-kartik-aaryan-sony-titu-sweety-new-chip-of-the-old-block-5133639/|archivedate=25 April 2018}}</ref> Both his parents are doctors; his father is a [[paediatrician]], and his mother, Mala, is a [[gynaecologist]]. He pursued an engineering degree in biotechnology from [[Navi Mumbai]]'s D Y Patil College of Engineering, while secretly harbouring ambitions for a career in film.<ref name=\"engineer\">{{cite web|title=The engineer who became a Bollywood hero|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-the-engineer-who-became-a-bollywood-hero/20140423.htm|publisher=Rediff.com|accessdate=23 April 2014|last=N|first=Patcy|date=7 February 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140423215510/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-the-engineer-who-became-a-bollywood-hero/20140423.htm|archivedate=23 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Rawal Kukreja|first=Monika|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/mother-s-day-kartik-aaryan-says-his-mom-googles-his-name-every-day-adds-his-girlfriends-on-facebook/story-d8HuZdZqZ4L3umZVmRHRjO.html|title=Mother\u2019s Day: Kartik Aaryan says his mom googles his name every day, adds his girlfriends on Facebook|work=[[Hindustan Times]]|date=13 May 2018|accessdate=3 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180702233234/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/mother-s-day-kartik-aaryan-says-his-mom-googles-his-name-every-day-adds-his-girlfriends-on-facebook/story-d8HuZdZqZ4L3umZVmRHRjO.html|archive-date=2 July 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> He has said that he would skip his classes and travel for two hours to attend auditions.<ref name=\"dna18\">{{cite news|last=Rakshit|first=Nayandeep|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/interview-sonu-ke-titu-ki-sweety-actor-kartik-aaryan-now-people-are-calling-me-a-hot-chocolate-boy-2587229|title=Sonu Ke Titu Ki Sweety actor Kartik Aaryan: Now, people are calling me a \u2018hot-chocolate boy\u2019|work=[[Daily News and Analysis]]|date=22 February 2018|accessdate=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180410062553/http://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/interview-sonu-ke-titu-ki-sweety-actor-kartik-aaryan-now-people-are-calling-me-a-hot-chocolate-boy-2587229|archivedate=10 April 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"firstpost18\">{{cite news|last=Srivastava|first=Abhishek|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/kartik-aaryan-says-contrary-to-popular-belief-sonu-ke-titu-ki-sweety-is-not-a-recreation-of-pyaar-ka-punchnama-4360615.html|title=Kartik Aaryan says contrary to popular belief, Sonu Ke Titu Ki Sweety is not a recreation of Pyaar Ka Punchnama|work=[[Firstpost]]|date=21 February 2018|accessdate=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180312140604/http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/kartik-aaryan-says-contrary-to-popular-belief-sonu-ke-titu-ki-sweety-is-not-a-recreation-of-pyaar-ka-punchnama-4360615.html|archivedate=12 March 2018}}</ref> Aaryan began a modelling career while in university and after three years of unsuccessfully auditioning for films, he did an acting course from the Kreating Charakters institute. He informed his parents of his desire to become an actor only after he signed his first film.<ref name=\"engineer\" /><ref name=\"filmfare14\">{{cite news|last=Loynmoon|first=Karishma|url=http://www.filmfare.com/interviews/i-didnt-know-how-to-kiss-5960.html|title=I didn't know how to kiss|work=[[Filmfare]]|date=24 April 2014|accessdate=27 February 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141020202103/http://www.filmfare.com/interviews/i-didnt-know-how-to-kiss-5960.html|archivedate=20 October 2014}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Kartik Aaryan in 2014.jpg|thumb|left|upright=0.9|Aaryan at an event for ''[[Kaanchi: The Unbreakable]]'' in 2014]]\n\nWhile still in his third year of college, Aaryan made his acting debut with [[Luv Ranjan]]'s [[buddy film]] ''[[Pyaar Ka Punchnama]]'' (2011), co-starring [[Divyendu Sharma]], Raayo S Bakhirta, and [[Nushrat Bharucha]], which revolves around the romantic tribulations faced by three young men.<ref name=\"gamble\">{{cite news|last=Khuranaa|first=Amann|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Kartik-Aaryan-My-mom-still-feels-that-being-in-films-is-a-gamble/articleshow/49481081.cms|title=Kartik Aaryan: My mom still feels that being in films is a gamble|work=[[The Times of India]]|date=21 October 2015|accessdate=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170726231045/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Kartik-Aaryan-My-mom-still-feels-that-being-in-films-is-a-gamble/articleshow/49481081.cms|archivedate=26 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=B-town's new faces in 2011|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/B-town-s-new-faces-in-2011-imagegallery-13-bollywood-lmvkDTgiejf.html|publisher=[[Sify]]|accessdate=10 January 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140418123136/http://www.sify.com/movies/B-town-s-new-faces-in-2011-imagegallery-13-bollywood-lmvkDTgiejf.html|archivedate=18 April 2014}}</ref> He found a casting call for the film on Facebook and secured the role after auditioning for six months.<ref name=\"engineer\" /> As he had limited financial means at that point, he lived in an apartment with 12 other aspiring actors and earned money by cooking for them.<ref name=\"engineer\" /><ref>{{cite news|last=Singh|first=Raghuvendra|url=https://www.filmfare.com/features/kartik-aaryan-interview-with-filmfare-12391-3.html|title=Kartik Aaryan reveals his food secrets|work=Filmfare|date=29 February 2016|accessdate=27 February 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170105025648/http://www.filmfare.com/features/kartik-aaryan-interview-with-filmfare-12391-3.html|archivedate=5 January 2017}}</ref> In ''Pyaar Ka Punchnama'', his character's four-minute [[monologue]] was one of the lengthiest single shots done for a Hindi film to that point.<ref>{{cite news|title=Debutant breaks record with four minute comic monologue?|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebrities/features/type/view/id/2205|author=Tuteja, Joginder|work=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|date=13 May 2011|accessdate=10 January 2013|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140325130540/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebrities/features/type/view/id/2205|archivedate=25 March 2014}}</ref> Reviewing it for [[Rediff.com]], Shaikh Ayaz found Aaryan's \"bursting soliloquy on why women are the way they are and can never be understood [to be] riotously funny\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Review: Pyaar Ka Punchnama could have been better|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-pyaar-ka-punchnama/20110520.htm|author=Ayaz, Shaikh|publisher=Rediff.com|date=20 May 2011|accessdate=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160307182653/http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-pyaar-ka-punchnama/20110520.htm|archivedate=7 March 2016}}</ref> [[Namrata Joshi]] of ''[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]]'' criticised the film for portraying each of the female characters as a \"hard-hearted bitch\" but was appreciative of Aaryan's monologue and the chemistry between the three men.<ref>{{cite news|title=Pyaar Ka Punchnama|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/magazine/story/pyaar-ka-punchnama/271980|author=[[Namrata Joshi|Joshi, Namrata]]|work=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]]|date=6 June 2011|accessdate=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180702192240/https://www.outlookindia.com/magazine/story/pyaar-ka-punchnama/271980|archivedate=2 July 2018}}</ref> The film emerged as a [[sleeper hit]] and he received a nomination for the [[Producers Guild Film Award for Best Male Debut]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Decoding the success of Pyaar Ka Punchnama: How it became a sleeper hit|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/decoding-the-success-of-pyaar-ka-punchnama-how-it-became-a-sleeper-hit/story-nSevPqlSEdlLWKYFampz0L.html|author=Vats, Rohit|work=Hindustan Times|date=22 February 2018|accessdate=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180321071600/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/decoding-the-success-of-pyaar-ka-punchnama-how-it-became-a-sleeper-hit/story-nSevPqlSEdlLWKYFampz0L.html|archivedate=21 March 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"pga12\">{{cite news|title=Nominations for 7th Chevrolet Apsara Film and Television Producers Guild Awards|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/features/nominations-for-7th-chevrolet-apsara-film-and-television-producers-guild-awards/|work=Bollywood Hungama|date=25 January 2012|accessdate=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180702100440/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/features/nominations-for-7th-chevrolet-apsara-film-and-television-producers-guild-awards/|archivedate=2 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nAfter the release of ''Pyaar Ka Punchnama'', Aaryan completed his engineering degree on the insistence of his mother.<ref name=\"firstpost18\" /><ref name=\"indiatoday15\" /><ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Its-nice-to-be-an-educated-actor-Kartik-Tiwari/articleshow/18333085.cms|title=It\u2019s nice to be an educated actor: Kartik Tiwari|work=The Times of India|accessdate=9 November 2017|date=5 February 2013|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171231001804/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Its-nice-to-be-an-educated-actor-Kartik-Tiwari/articleshow/18333085.cms|archivedate=31 December 2017}}</ref> His next film release came two years later when he collaborated once again with Ranjan and Bharucha in the romance ''[[Akaash Vani]]'' (2013), which is about the titular lovers who are separated when Vani is married off to an abusive husband.<ref>{{cite news|title='Akash Vani' will make a mark as love story: Abhishek Pathak|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-12-06/news-interviews/35646472_1_love-story-pyaar-ka-punchnama-luv-ranjan|work=The Times of India|date=6 December 2012|accessdate=10 January 2013}}</ref><ref>\n{{cite news|title=Ten films that weren\u2019t really what they seemed|url=https://www.livemint.com/Leisure/0yMeeGFzUpYiRkrHnU0IUI/Ten-films-that-werent-really-what-they-seemed.html|work=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]]|author=Jha, Lata|date=9 December 2015|accessdate=10 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190110235115/https://www.livemint.com/Leisure/0yMeeGFzUpYiRkrHnU0IUI/Ten-films-that-werent-really-what-they-seemed.html|archive-date=10 January 2019|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}\n</ref> [[Sudhish Kamath]] of ''[[The Hindu]]'' praised the film for exploring chauvinism in India, a rare concept for Hindi film, and praised the chemistry between the two stars, writing that \"you can tell how much they are in love, even when they don't have any lines\".<ref>{{cite news|title=Akaash Vani \u2014 Far removed from Bollywood better|url=https://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/akaash-vani-far-removed-from-bollywood/article4348025.ece|author=[[Sudhish Kamath|Kamath, Sudish]]|work=[[The Hindu]]|date=26 January 2013|accessdate=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171125063500/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/akaash-vani-far-removed-from-bollywood/article4348025.ece|archivedate=25 November 2017}}</ref> Sudhir Chaudhary, the cinematographer in Aaryan's previous films, showed his work to [[Subhash Ghai]], who was impressed by Aaryan and cast him in his directorial ''[[Kaanchi: The Unbreakable]]'' (2014).<ref name=\"filmfare14\" /> It is a drama about a woman's quest for justice when her husband is murdered by politicians, in which Aaryan played the love interest of the title character (played by [[Mishti]]). Despite a brief role, Aaryan agreed to the project to work with Ghai.<ref name=\"filmfare14\" /> Saibal Chatterjee of [[NDTV]] disliked the film but wrote that Aaryan \"exudes strong screen presence and shows flashes of qualities needed to be a mainstream Bollywood lover boy\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Kaanchi movie review|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/kaanchi-movie-review-957|author=Chatterjee, Saibal|publisher=[[NDTV]]|date=8 May 2014|accessdate=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171114205137/http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/kaanchi-movie-review-957|archivedate=14 November 2017}}</ref> Both ''Akaash Vani'' and ''Kaanchi'' did not perform well commercially, leading Aaryan to question his career prospects.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://boxofficeindia.com/actor.php?actorid=634|title=Kartik Tiwari|accessdate=2 July 2018|website=[[Box Office India]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180702100436/https://boxofficeindia.com/actor.php?actorid=634|archive-date=2 July 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"indiatoday15\">{{cite news|title=Kartik Aaryan: Thankfully, people haven't yet called Pyaar Ka Punchnama 2 misogynistic|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/kartik-aaryan-thankfully-people-havent-yet-called-pyaar-ka-punchnama-2-misogynistic-problem-yeh-hai-ki-woh-ladki-hai-pkp-2-release-kartik-tiwari-interview-268086-2015-10-14|author=Bhattacharya, Ananya|work=[[India Today]]|date=14 October 2015|accessdate=2 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180702161610/https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/kartik-aaryan-thankfully-people-havent-yet-called-pyaar-ka-punchnama-2-misogynistic-problem-yeh-hai-ki-woh-ladki-hai-pkp-2-release-kartik-tiwari-interview-268086-2015-10-14|archive-date=2 July 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, Aaryan starred in Ranjan's comedy sequel ''[[Pyaar Ka Punchnama 2]]'', which retained some of the original's cast, including him and Bharucha, and added the actors [[Omkar Kapoor]] and [[Sunny Nijar|Sunny Singh]]. In it, he delivered an even longer, seven minute single-shot monologue.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/kartik-aaryan-on-his-single-status-girls-took-my-love-rant-monologue-too-seriously/story-jtudBR9HbEKWI9gBG3borO.html|title=Kartik Aaryan on his single status: Girls took my love rant monologue too seriously|work=Hindustan Times|accessdate=9 November 2017|date=29 July 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171110004816/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/kartik-aaryan-on-his-single-status-girls-took-my-love-rant-monologue-too-seriously/story-jtudBR9HbEKWI9gBG3borO.html|archivedate=10 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/What-makes-Kartik-Aaryan-the-monologue-king/articleshow/50558928.cms|title=What makes Kartik Aaryan the monologue king?|work=The Times of India|date=17 January 2017|access-date=30 November 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160116075410/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/What-makes-Kartik-Aaryan-the-monologue-king/articleshow/50558928.cms|archivedate=16 January 2016}}</ref> Mike McCahill of ''[[The Guardian]]'' criticised the film's poor handling of female roles, but considered the banter between Aaryan and Bharucha's characters to be its highlight.<ref>{{cite news|title=Pyaar Ka Punchnama 2 review \u2013 second helping of The Hangover, Bollywood-style, turns nasty at the end|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/oct/18/pkp2-pyaar-ka-punchnama-2-review-bollywood-india-hangover|author=McCahill, Mike|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=18 October 2015|accessdate=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171205121839/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/oct/18/pkp2-pyaar-ka-punchnama-2-review-bollywood-india-hangover|archivedate=5 December 2017}}</ref> Shubha Shetty-Guha of ''[[Mid Day]]'' too took note of the misogynistic themes but found parts of it \"uproariously funny\".<ref>{{cite news|title='Pyaar Ka Punchnama 2' \u2013 Movie Review|url=https://www.mid-day.com/articles/pyaar-ka-punchnama-2---movie-review/16612213|author=Shetty-Guha, Shubha|work=[[Mid Day]]|date=16 October 2015|accessdate=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171206091016/http://www.mid-day.com/articles/pyaar-ka-punchnama-2---movie-review/16612213|archivedate=6 December 2017}}</ref> When asked about the sexism in the film, Aaryan said that as a proponent of gender equality his character did not reflect his personal beliefs.<ref>{{cite web|title=I respect women a lot, hold no grudges against them: Kartik Aaryan on his 'PKP2' monologue|url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/i-respect-women-a-lot-hold-no-grudges-against-them-kartik-aaryan-on-his-pkp2-monologue-1157913.html|author=Sameeksha|publisher=[[CNN-News18]]|date=29 October 2015|accessdate=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180702192241/https://www.news18.com/news/movies/i-respect-women-a-lot-hold-no-grudges-against-them-kartik-aaryan-on-his-pkp2-monologue-1157913.html|archivedate=2 July 2018}}</ref> With earnings of over {{INRConvert|880|m}} against a budget of {{INRConvert|220|m}}, ''Pyaar Ka Punchnama 2'' emerged as a major financial success.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://boxofficeindia.com/movie.php?movieid=3083|title=Pyaar Ka Punchnama 2|accessdate=2 July 2018|website=Box Office India|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171217155158/http://boxofficeindia.com/movie.php?movieid=3083|archivedate=17 December 2017}}</ref> For his performance, Aaryan won a [[Stardust Award]] for Best Actor In A Comic Role.<ref name=\"first award\">{{cite news|title=Kartik Aaryan Ecstatic With First Award|url=https://www.mid-day.com/articles/kartik-aaryan-ecstatic-with-first-award/16798161|work=Mid Day|date=23 December 2015|accessdate=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180702100440/https://www.mid-day.com/articles/kartik-aaryan-ecstatic-with-first-award/16798161|archivedate=2 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe following year, Aaryan featured as a young Muslim boy who falls in love with an older woman in [[Tanuja Chandra]]'s short film ''Silvat'', which was made as part of the Zeal For Unity initiative to bridge cultural barriers between India and Pakistan.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/kartik-aaryan-plays-muslim-boy-in-tanuja-chandras-film/|title=Kartik Aaryan plays Muslim boy in Tanuja Chandra\u2019s film|date=18 February 2016|work=The Indian Express|access-date=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180317164658/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/kartik-aaryan-plays-muslim-boy-in-tanuja-chandras-film/|archivedate=17 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/entertainment-others/in-zeal-for-unity-indian-pakistani-filmmakers-to-bridge-divide/|title=In \u2018zeal for unity\u2019, Indian, Pakistani filmmakers to bridge divide|date=10 February 2016|work=The Indian Express|access-date=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160526043712/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/entertainment-others/in-zeal-for-unity-indian-pakistani-filmmakers-to-bridge-divide/|archivedate=26 May 2016}}</ref> As he enjoyed working in comedies, Aaryan next starred alongside [[Paresh Rawal]] and [[Kriti Kharbanda]] in ''[[Guest iin London]]'' (2017), which is about a young couple troubled by unwelcome guests.<ref name=\"guest\">{{cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/guest-iin-london-actor-kartik-aaryan-4724703/|title=Guest Iin London actor Kartik Aaryan: It is important to have an image in the industry|date=27 June 2017|work=The Indian Express|access-date=3 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171207141240/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/guest-iin-london-actor-kartik-aaryan-4724703/|archivedate=7 December 2017}}</ref> A few scenes between Rawal and him were improvised on set.<ref name=\"guest\" /> In a scathing review, Rohit Vats of ''[[Hindustan Times]]'' criticised the film's reliance on [[flatulence humour]], and wrote that Aaryan \"looks good, dances well, does his gags well, but eventually ends up playing the second fiddle to Rawal. Kartik has a likeable vibe, but that gets drowned in Rawal\u2019s perennial farting.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=Guest Iin London movie review: Don\u2019t make silly films like Paresh Rawal|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/movie-reviews/guest-iin-london-movie-review-paresh-rawal-s-lame-jokes-make-everything-look-silly/story-8ANuWD0BvHN0AzyipIo0eM.html|author=Vats, Rohit|work=Hindustan Times|date=20 July 2017|accessdate=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180130234143/https://www.hindustantimes.com/movie-reviews/guest-iin-london-movie-review-paresh-rawal-s-lame-jokes-make-everything-look-silly/story-8ANuWD0BvHN0AzyipIo0eM.html|archivedate=30 January 2018}}</ref> It did not perform well commercially.<ref>{{cite web|title=Box Office: Mom opens poorly, Guest Iin London flops|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/box-office-mom-opens-poorly-guest-iin-london-flops/20170710.htm|publisher=Rediff.com|date=10 July 2017|accessdate=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170928125220/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/box-office-mom-opens-poorly-guest-iin-london-flops/20170710.htm|archivedate=28 September 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Commercial success (2018\u2013present) ===\n[[File:Nushrat-Bharucha-and-Kartik-Aaryan-on-the-sets-of-Indias-Next-Superstars-1 (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright=0.9|Aaryan and [[Nushrat Bharucha]], pictured in 2018, have collaborated on four films, including ''[[Sonu Ke Titu Ki Sweety]]'']]\nAaryan's breakthrough came in 2018 when he collaborated with Ranjan and Bharucha for the fourth time in ''[[Sonu Ke Titu Ki Sweety]]'', which also reunited him with Sunny Singh.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/kartik-aaryan-luv-ranjan-reunite-for-a-rom-com-116110701489_1.html|title=Kartik Aaryan, Luv Ranjan reunite for a rom-com|date=7 November 2016|work=[[Business Standard]]|access-date=30 November 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161201015858/http://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/kartik-aaryan-luv-ranjan-reunite-for-a-rom-com-116110701489_1.html|archivedate=1 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=\"It\u2019s finally happening to me\" \u2013 Kartik Aaryan|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/features/finally-happening-kartik-aaryan/|author=Jha, Subhash K.|work=Bollywood Hungama|date=17 March 2018|accessdate=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180317084937/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/features/finally-happening-kartik-aaryan/|archivedate=17 March 2018}}</ref> It tells the story of Sonu (Aaryan) who plots to separate his best friend (Singh) from his fianc\u00e9e (Bharucha) as Sonu considers her to be a [[gold digger]]. As with the ''Pyaar Ka Punchnama'' films, reviewers criticised the film's misogyny;<ref>{{cite news|title=Luv Ranjan on the alleged misogyny in Sonu Ke Titu Ki Sweety: Political correctness is not always a great thing|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/sonu-ke-titu-ki-sweety-director-luv-ranjan-5095502/|author=Jalan, Shivangi|work=The Indian Express|date=13 March 2018|accessdate=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180313043106/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/sonu-ke-titu-ki-sweety-director-luv-ranjan-5095502/|archivedate=13 March 2018}}</ref> [[Anna M. M. Vetticad]] of ''[[Firstpost]]'' took note of the film's homosexual undertones but panned it as a \"dreary woman-hate-fest\" and thought that Aaryan was \"tiresome and hammy\" in it.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sonu Ke Titu Ki Sweety movie review: A dreary woman-hate-fest cum unwitting gaymance|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/sonu-ke-titu-ki-sweety-movie-review-a-dreary-woman-hate-fest-cum-unwitting-gaymance-4363591.html|author=[[Anna M. M. Vetticad|Vetticad, Anna M. M.]]|work=Firstpost|date=23 February 2018|accessdate=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180624231650/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/sonu-ke-titu-ki-sweety-movie-review-a-dreary-woman-hate-fest-cum-unwitting-gaymance-4363591.html|archivedate=24 June 2018}}</ref> [[Rajeev Masand]] too disliked the \"objectionable stereotyping\" of women but found it to be \"unquestionably funny\" and credited Aaryan for making his character a \"relatable, likeable figure despite his misdeeds\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Sonu Ke Titu Ki Sweety Review: Despite Its Stereotyping & Frequent Misogyny, The Film Is Unquestionably Funny|url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/sonu-ke-titu-ki-sweety-review-despite-its-sexism-stereotyping-frequent-misogyny-the-film-is-unquestionably-funny-1670911.html|author=[[Rajeev Masand|Masand, Rajeev]]|publisher=CNN-News18|date=24 February 2018|accessdate=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180224111052/http://www.news18.com/news/movies/sonu-ke-titu-ki-sweety-review-despite-its-sexism-stereotyping-frequent-misogyny-the-film-is-unquestionably-funny-1670911.html|archivedate=24 February 2018}}</ref> Once again addressing the criticisms, Aaryan said that portraying women as negative characters did not amount to misogyny just as casting men in villainous roles did not amount to misandry.<ref name=\"chip\" /><ref>{{cite news|title=Kartik Aaryan raises an important question about his film being called \"sexist\"!|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/kartik-aaryan-raises-an-important-question-about-his-film-being-called-sexist/articleshow/63729949.cms|work=The Times of India|date=12 April 2018|accessdate=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180702174146/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/kartik-aaryan-raises-an-important-question-about-his-film-being-called-sexist/articleshow/63729949.cms|archivedate=2 July 2018}}</ref> With earnings of {{INRConvert|1.5|b}}, the film emerged as Aaryan's biggest success.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/box-office-report-sonu-ke-titu-ki-sweety-is-super-hit-earns-over-rs-68-crore-1820403|title=Box Office Report: Sonu Ke Titu Ki Sweety Is 'Super Hit.' Earns Over Rs. 68 Crore|date=7 March 2018|publisher=NDTV|access-date=10 March 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180310075814/https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/box-office-report-sonu-ke-titu-ki-sweety-is-super-hit-earns-over-rs-68-crore-1820403|archivedate=10 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://boxofficeindia.com/report-details.php?articleid=3881|title=Worldwide Alltime : Padmaavat 7th \u2013 Baaghi 2 22nd|accessdate=26 April 2018|date=26 April 2018|website=Box Office India|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20190111163826/https://boxofficeindia.com/report-details.php?articleid=3881|archivedate=11 January 2019|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nAaryan believed that the success of ''Sonu Ke Titu Ki Sweety'' allowed him to choose from a wider variety of roles. He was drawn to ''[[Luka Chuppi]]'' (2019), a satire on live-in relationships in small-town India, for depicting social issues through comedy.<ref name=\"telegraph\">{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/entertainment/a-fan-wanted-to-eat-my-hair-kartik-aaryan/cid/1685937|title=A fan wanted to eat my hair: Kartik Aaryan|last=Upadhyay|first=Karishma|date=1 March 2019|work=[[The Telegraph (Calcutta)|The Telegraph]]|access-date=1 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190301031333/https://www.telegraphindia.com/entertainment/a-fan-wanted-to-eat-my-hair-kartik-aaryan/cid/1685937|archive-date=1 March 2019|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Co-starring [[Kriti Sanon]], it was filmed in his hometown of Gwalior.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/kartik-aaryan-luka-chuppi-release-bollywood-mumbai-5602183/|title=Don\u2019t let rejection bring you down: Luka Chuppi actor Kartik Aaryan|last=Khatau|first=Parth|date=27 February 2019|work=The Indian Express|access-date=1 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190301140210/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/kartik-aaryan-luka-chuppi-release-bollywood-mumbai-5602183/|archive-date=1 March 2019|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Shubhra Gupta of ''[[The Indian Express]]'' criticised the writing for failing to subvert the issues raised in the film, and thought that both Aaryan and Sanon \"come off standard-issue Bollywood\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/luka-chuppi-review-kartik-aaryan-kriti-sanon-5606425/|title=Luka Chuppi movie review: A wasted opportunity|last=Gupta|first=Shubhra|date=1 March 2019|work=The Indian Express|access-date=1 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190301103733/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/luka-chuppi-review-kartik-aaryan-kriti-sanon-5606425/|archive-date=1 March 2019|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> He next starred alongside [[Bhumi Pednekar]] and [[Ananya Panday]] in the comedy ''[[Pati Patni Aur Woh (2019 film)|Pati Patni Aur Woh]]'', a remake of the 1978 [[Pati Patni Aur Woh|film of the same name]]. He took on the part of a philandering husband, which was played by [[Sanjeev Kumar]] in the original film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/kartik-aaryan-teams-up-with-ananya-panday-and-bhumi-pednekar-for-pati-patni-aur-woh-2007209.html|title=Kartik Aaryan Teams Up with Ananya Panday and Bhumi Pednekar for Pati Patni Aur Woh|date=19 January 2019|publisher=CNN-News18|access-date=19 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190119120849/https://www.news18.com/news/movies/kartik-aaryan-teams-up-with-ananya-panday-and-bhumi-pednekar-for-pati-patni-aur-woh-2007209.html|archive-date=19 January 2019|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> [[Anupama Chopra]] considered the film to be less misogynistic than the original; she wrote that Aaryan \"enthusiastically commits\" to his part but added that he had been overshadowed by his leading ladies.<ref>{{cite web|author=Chopra, Anupama|url=https://www.filmcompanion.in/pati-patni-aur-woh-movie-review-fun-but-too-lightweight-and-low-iq-to-carry-complex-ideas|title=Pati Patni Aur Woh Movie Review: Fun, But Too Lightweight And Low IQ To Carry Complex Ideas|date=6 December 2019|website=Film Companion|access-date=6 December 2019}}</ref> Both ''Luka Chuppi'' and ''Pati Patni Aur Woh'' were commercially successful, each grossing over {{INRConvert|1|b}} worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|author=Tuteja, Joginder|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/box-office-special-features/box-office-kartik-aaryan-ananya-pandey-bhumi-pednekar-mudassar-azizs-stocks-go-pati-patni-aur-woh-week-two-updates/|title=Box Office \u2013 Kartik Aaryan, Ananya Pandey, Bhumi Pednekar, Mudassar Aziz\u2019s stocks go up with Pati Patni aur Woh \u2013 Week two updates|date=20 December 2019|website=Bollywood Hungama|access-date=20 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/box-office-collections/worldwide/2019/|title=Bollywood Top Grossers Worldwide: 2019|website=Bollywood Hungama|access-date=20 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[Imtiaz Ali (director)|Imtiaz Ali]]'s romantic drama ''[[Love Aaj Kal (2020 film)|Love Aaj Kal]]'', a [[spiritual successor]] to Ali's [[Love Aaj Kal|2009 film of the same name]] marked Aaryan's first film release of 2020.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/entertainment/entertainment-news/love-aaj-kal-box-office-preview-kartik-aaryan-and-sara-ali-khan-starrer-to-make-terrific-start-804269.html|title='Love Aaj Kal' box office preview: Kartik Aaryan And Sara Ali Khan starrer to make terrific start|last=Roktim|first=Rajpal|date=13 February 2020|work=Deccan Herald|access-date=14 February 2020}}</ref> In it he played dual roles of young men in 1990 and 2020, opposite the actresses [[Aarushi Sharma]] and [[Sara Ali Khan]], respectively. He worked on the mannerisms and body language of the characters to differentiate them from each other.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/bollywood/kartik-aryan-on-love-aaj-kal-im-working-out-of-my-comfort-zone-for-the-first-time-and-its-a-litmus-test-for-me-8034121.html|title=Kartik Aryan on Love Aaj Kal: I'm working out of my comfort zone for the first time and it\u2019s a litmus test for me|last=Sinha|first=Seema|date=13 February 2020|website=Firstpost|access-date=14 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/features/meet-kartik-aaryan-veer-raghu-imtiaz-alis-love-aaj-kal/|title=Meet Kartik Aaryan as Veer and Raghu in Imtiaz Ali\u2019s Love Aaj Kal|date=21 January 2020|website=Bollywood Hungama|access-date=14 February 2020}}</ref> In a negative review of the film, Nandini Ramnath of [[Scroll.in]] wrote that Aaryan \"nails the diffidence and callowness of his characters\" but bemoaned that he lacked \"brooding quality and simmering intensity\" in certain scenes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://scroll.in/reel/952921/love-aaj-kal-movie-review-a-banal-and-self-indulgent-tour-of-past-and-present-romance|title=\u2018Love Aaj Kal\u2019 movie review: A banal and self-indulgent tour of past and present romance|date=14 February 2020|website=[[Scroll.in]]|access-date=14 February 2020}}</ref> It emerged as a [[box office bomb]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nationalheraldindia.com/entertainment/love-aaj-kal-flops-trade-analysts-speak|title=\u2018Love Aaj Kal\u2019 flops, trade analysts speak|last=Jha|first=Subhash K|date=19 February 2020|work=[[National Herald (India)|National Herald]]|access-date=21 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nAaryan will next star in standalone sequels to the 2007 comedy horror film ''[[Bhool Bhulaiyaa]]'' and the 2008 romantic comedy ''[[Dostana (2008 film)|Dostana]]'', entitled ''[[Bhool Bhulaiyaa 2]]'' and ''[[Dostana 2]]'', respectively.<ref>{{cite web|author=Basu, Nilanjana|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/bhool-bhulaiyaa-2-first-look-kartik-aaryan-is-almost-akshay-kumars-doppelganger-2086984|title=Bhool Bhulaiyaa 2 First Look: Kartik Aaryan Is (Almost) Akshay Kumar's Doppelganger|date=19 August 2019|website=NDTV|access-date=19 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/dostana-2-kartik-aaryan-janhvi-kapoor-roped-in-as-leads-search-on-for-second-suitable-boy-in-karan-johar-film/story-pS72JdUXgfvzJoDolMHDcP.html|title=Dostana 2: Kartik Aaryan, Janhvi Kapoor roped in as leads, search on for second \u2018suitable boy\u2019 in Karan Johar film|date=27 June 2019|work=Hindustan Times|access-date=27 June 2019}}</ref> He has also committed to headline an as-yet untitled action film directed by [[Om Raut]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/kartik-aaryan-to-star-in-om-rauts-3d-action-film/articleshow/74041275.cms|title=Kartik Aaryan to star in Om Raut's 3D action film|date=9 February 2020|work=Mumbai Mirror|access-date=10 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Other work and media image ==\nIn addition to acting in films, Aaryan endorses several brands and products, including the sportswear brand [[Hummel International]], the cream [[Emami#Fair And Handsome|Emami Fair And Handsome]] and the clothing brand [[Manyavar]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ani/hummel-signs-bollywood-heartthrob-kartik-aaryan-as-india-brand-ambassador-119021600296_1.html|title=hummel signs bollywood heartthrob, Kartik Aaryan as India Brand Ambassador|date=16 February 2019|work=[[Business Standard]]|access-date=20 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://brandequity.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/advertising/actor-kartik-aaryan-to-endorse-emami-fair-and-handsome/64168970|title=Actor Kartik Aaryan to endorse Emami Fair And Handsome|date=15 May 2018|work=[[The Economic Times]]|access-date=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180625100146/https://brandequity.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/advertising/actor-kartik-aaryan-to-endorse-emami-fair-and-handsome/64168970|archivedate=25 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/kartik-aaryan-appointed-new-face-ethnic-brand-manyavar/|title=Kartik Aaryan appointed as the new face of ethnic brand Manyavar|date=4 July 2019|work=Bollywood Hungama|access-date=6 July 2019}}</ref> He has also co-hosted the [[19th IIFA Awards|2018 IIFA Awards]] with [[Ayushmann Khurrana]], and the [[Zee Cine Awards|2019 Zee Cine Awards]] with [[Vicky Kaushal]].<ref name=\"zee\"/><ref name=\"iifa\">{{cite news|last=Roy|first=Priyanka|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/entertainment/the-big-bolly-show-241387|title=The Big Bolly Show|work=[[The Telegraph (Calcutta)|The Telegraph]]|date=1 July 2018|accessdate=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180702102355/https://www.telegraphindia.com/entertainment/the-big-bolly-show-241387|archivedate=2 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Aaryan became a member of the All Stars Football Club, which organises football matches for charity.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/kartikaaryanin-all-stars-football-club/article8529466.ece|title=Kartik Aaryan in All Stars Football Club|work=The Hindu|accessdate=2 July 2018|date=28 April 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190111164110/https://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/kartikaaryanin-all-stars-football-club/article8529466.ece|archivedate=11 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> He participated with several other celebrities, including [[Ranbir Kapoor]], for a tournament held in New Delhi the following year.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Kartik-Aryan-flies-to-New-Delhi-with-Ranbir-Kapoor-for-a-charity-football-match/articleshow/53399448.cms|title=Kartik Aryan flies to New Delhi with Ranbir Kapoor for a charity football match!|date=28 January 2017|work=The Times of India|access-date=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170517190557/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Kartik-Aryan-flies-to-New-Delhi-with-Ranbir-Kapoor-for-a-charity-football-match/articleshow/53399448.cms|archivedate=17 May 2017}}</ref> Aaryan was scheduled to take part in the club's next tournament, held in Singapore in 2018, but had to back out after dislocating his toe during practice.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/this-is-why-kartik-aaryan-will-have-to-ditch-a-charity-event-involving-arjun-and-ranbir-kapoor/articleshow/63817069.cms|title=This is why Kartik Aaryan will have to ditch a charity event involving Arjun and Ranbir Kapoor|date=18 April 2018|work=The Times of India|access-date=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180420122845/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/this-is-why-kartik-aaryan-will-have-to-ditch-a-charity-event-involving-arjun-and-ranbir-kapoor/articleshow/63817069.cms|archivedate=20 April 2018}}</ref> In 2018, Aaryan raised awareness on [[plastic pollution]] during [[World Environment Day]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/interview-world-environment-day-kartik-aaryan-i-stopped-using-plastic-bottles-5-years-ago-2622043|title=World Environment Day: Kartik Aaryan, \u2018I stopped using plastic bottles 5 years ago\u2019|date=5 June 2018|work=Daily News and Analysis|access-date=2 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180702150613/http://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/interview-world-environment-day-kartik-aaryan-i-stopped-using-plastic-bottles-5-years-ago-2622043|archive-date=2 July 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The following year, the [[Election Commission of India]] appointed him to raise awareness on voter participation in his home state of Madhya Pradesh.<ref>{{cite news|author=Roy, Dhaval|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-lok-sabha-election-2019-kartik-aaryan-becomes-the-state-icon-of-madhya-pradesh-2738992|title=Lok Sabha Election 2019: Kartik Aaryan becomes the state icon of Madhya Pradesh|date=13 April 2019|work=Daily News and Analysis|access-date=13 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nAaryan was placed eighth in ''[[The Times of India]]''{{'}}s listing of the country's most desirable men of 2018.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/vicky-kaushal-is-the-times-most-desirable-man-of-2018/articleshow/69361561.cms|title=Meet India\u2019s most desirable dudes|date=17 May 2019|work=The Times of India|access-date=21 December 2019}}</ref> In 2019, he appeared in ''[[Forbes India]]''{{'s}} [[Forbes Celebrity 100|Celebrity 100]] list, ranking 67th with an estimated annual income of {{INRConvert|103.8|m}}.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.forbesindia.com/lists/2019-celebrity-100/1819/all |title=2019 Celebrity 100 |work=Forbes India |accessdate=20 December 2018 }}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n[[File:Celebrities-grace-Lux-Golden-Rose-Awards-2016-35.jpg|thumb|Aaryan at an event for [[Lux (soap)|Lux]] in 2016]]\n\n=== Film ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Key\n| style=\"background:#ffc;\"| {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\"|Year\n! scope=\"col\"|Film\n! scope=\"col\"|Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" scope=\"col\"|Notes\n|-\n| 2011\n!scope=\"row\"| ''[[Pyaar Ka Punchnama]]''\n| Rajat (Rajjo)\n|\n|-\n| 2013\n!scope=\"row\"| ''[[Akaash Vani]]''\n| Akaash\n|\n|-\n| 2014\n!scope=\"row\"| ''[[Kaanchi: The Unbreakable]]''\n| Binda\n|\n|-\n| 2015\n!scope=\"row\"| ''[[Pyaar Ka Punchnama 2]]''\n| Anshul (Gogo)\n|\n|-\n| 2016\n!scope=\"row\"| ''Silvat''\n| Anwar\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2017\n!scope