{"title_page": "The Purple Parade", "text_new": "{{Infobox recurring event\n|name              = The Purple Parade\n|native_name       = \n|native_name_lang  = \n|logo              = File:The_Purple_Parade_Logo.png\n|logo_alt          =\n|logo_caption      = \n|logo_size         =\n|image             = \n|image_size        =\n|alt               =\n|caption           = \n|status            = active\n|genre             = [[Disability rights movement]]\n|dates             = {{unbulleted list\n|{{start date|df=yes|2013|11|30}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|2014|11|15}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|2015|10|31}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|2016|11|05}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|2017|10|28}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|2018|10|27}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|2019|11|02}}\n}}\n|begins            = {{start date|df=yes|2013|11|30}}\n|ends              = <!-- {{end date|df=yes|YYYY|mm|dd}} -->\n|frequency         = Annual\n|venue             = [[Speakers' Corner, Singapore]], [[Hong Lim Park]] (from 2013 to 2015)<br>[[Fountain of Wealth]], [[Suntec City]] (since 2016)\n|country           = [[Singapore]]\n|years_active      = {{age|2013|11|30}}\n|first             = 2013\n|founder_name      = \n|last              = \n|prev              = {{start date|df=yes|2019|11|02}}\n|next              = TBA\n|participants      = \n|attendance        = \n|capacity          =\n|area              = \n|budget            = \n|activity          = \n|leader_name       =\n|patron            = \n|organised         = \n|filing            = \n|people            = \n|member            = \n|sponsor           = \n|sponsors           = \n|website           = {{URL|purpleparade.sg}}\n|current           = \n|footnotes         = \n}}\n\n'''The Purple Parade''' is an annual event that started in 2013 to raise awareness and campaign for inclusion of the [[disability in Singapore|disabled]] in Singapore. Events usually take place in a carnival-like format with many booths from different companies, performers from various [[list of disability organisations in Singapore|disability organisations in Singapore]], as well as the marching of contingents.\n\nThe event has been held each year in Singapore from 2013 to 2015 at [[Speakers Corner]] in [[Hong Lim Park]], as well as the [[Fountain of Wealth]] in [[Suntec City]] since 2016 on a Saturday in October or November. The 2019 event was held on 2 November.\n\n==History==\nThe Purple Parade was first conceived as an event for the inclusion of people with special needs back in 2013, with 40 organisations and the [[Central Singapore Community Development Council]] coming together to commemorate the [[International Day of Persons with Disabilities]], which falls on 3 December every year. In previous years, various organisations celebrated that in small groups, rendering the approach ineffective and without impact. In order to promote the event, a social media movement led by [[Denise Phua]], along with several [[list of members of the 12th Parliament of Singapore|parliamentarians]] (including [[Prime Minister of Singapore]] [[Lee Hsien Loong]] and then Acting [[Ministry of Culture, Community and Youth|Minister for Culture, Community and Youth]] [[Lawrence Wong]]) was started to get support for the event.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kok |first1=Xing Hui |title=40 organisations band together for disabled people |url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/40-organisations-band-together-disabled-people |website=Today |accessdate=24 April 2020 |date=29 November 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Kok |first1=Xing Hui |title=Purple Parade publicises through social media |url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/purple-parade-publicises-through-social-media |website=Today |accessdate=24 April 2020 |date=29 November 2013}}</ref> The first event was eventually held on 30 November 2013.<ref name=\"PP2013\">{{cite web |last1=Sim |first1=Royston |title=Over 4,000 turn up at event to raise awareness about special needs community |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/over-4000-turn-up-at-event-to-raise-awareness-about-special-needs-community |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=24 April 2020 |date=1 December 2013}}</ref>\n\nThe colour purple symbolises royalty, with the square logo representing a call for equality for those with special needs in all areas of society.<ref name=\"PP2013\"/>\n\nSince then, a total of seven Purple Parade events have been held in Singapore, occurring annually on Saturdays in October or November.\n\n==Events==\nEach event took place on a Saturday. It was held at Speakers' Corner in Hong Lim Park from 2013 to 2015, and at the Fountain of Wealth in Suntec City from 2016 to 2019.\n\n===The Purple Parade 2013===\nThe Purple Parade 2013 was held on 30 November 2013. Despite rainy weather, the event attracted a turnout of 4,000 people and pledges that formed a large square at Hong Lim Park. A carnival was organised as part of the event to showcase talents of those with special needs, as well as several performances that were held too. The success of this event prompted organisers to make the event a yearly affair, with more initiatives to support the community.<ref name=\"PP2013\"/>\n\n===The Purple Parade 2014===\n\n===The Purple Parade 2015===\n\n===The Purple Parade 2016===\n\n===The Purple Parade 2017===\n\n===The Purple Parade 2018===\n\n===The Purple Parade 2019===\n\n==Impact==\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of disability organisations in Singapore]]\n* [[List of social service agencies in Singapore]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.purpleparade.sg The Purple Parade]\n\n[[Category:2013 establishments in Singapore]]\n[[Category:Disability in Singapore]]\n[[Category:Disability organisations based in Singapore]]\n[[Category:Human rights in Singapore]]\n[[Category:Recurring events established in 2013]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox recurring event\n|name              = The Purple Parade\n|native_name       = \n|native_name_lang  = \n|logo              = File:The_Purple_Parade_Logo.png\n|logo_alt          =\n|logo_caption      = \n|logo_size         =\n|image             = \n|image_size        =\n|alt               =\n|caption           = \n|status            = active\n|genre             = [[Disability rights movement]]\n|dates             = {{unbulleted list\n|{{start date|df=yes|2013|11|30}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|2014|11|15}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|2015|10|31}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|2016|11|05}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|2017|10|28}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|2018|10|27}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|2019|11|02}}\n}}\n|begins            = {{start date|df=yes|2013|11|30}}\n|ends              = <!-- {{end date|df=yes|YYYY|mm|dd}} -->\n|frequency         = Annual\n|venue             = [[Speakers' Corner, Singapore]], [[Hong Lim Park]] (from 2013 to 2015)<br>[[Fountain of Wealth]], [[Suntec City]] (since 2016)\n|country           = [[Singapore]]\n|years_active      = {{age|2013|11|30}}\n|first             = 2013\n|founder_name      = \n|last              = \n|prev              = {{start date|df=yes|2019|11|02}}\n|next              = TBA\n|participants      = \n|attendance        = \n|capacity          =\n|area              = \n|budget            = \n|activity          = \n|leader_name       =\n|patron            = \n|organised         = \n|filing            = \n|people            = \n|member            = \n|sponsor           = \n|sponsors           = \n|website           = {{URL|purpleparade.sg}}\n|current           = \n|footnotes         = \n}}\n\n'''The Purple Parade''' is an annual event that started in 2013 to raise awareness and campaign for inclusion of the [[disability in Singapore|disabled]] in Singapore. Events usually take place in a carnival-like format with many booths from different companies, performers from various [[list of disability organisations in Singapore|disability organisations in Singapore]], as well as the marching of contingents.\n\nThe event has been held each year in Singapore from 2013 to 2015 at [[Speakers Corner]] in [[Hong Lim Park]], as well as the [[Fountain of Wealth]] in [[Suntec City]] on a Saturday in October or November. The 2019 event was held on 2 November.\n\n==History==\nThe Purple Parade was first conceived as an event for the inclusion of people with special needs back in 2013, with 40 organisations and the [[Central Singapore Community Development Council]] coming together to commemorate the [[International Day of Persons with Disabilities]], which falls on 3 December every year. In previous years, various organisations celebrated that in small groups, rendering the approach ineffective and without impact. In order to promote the event, a social media movement led by [[Denise Phua]], along with several [[list of members of the 12th Parliament of Singapore|parliamentarians]] (including [[Prime Minister of Singapore]] [[Lee Hsien Loong]] and then Acting [[Ministry of Culture, Community and Youth|Minister for Culture, Community and Youth]] [[Lawrence Wong]]) was started to get support for the event.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kok |first1=Xing Hui |title=40 organisations band together for disabled people |url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/40-organisations-band-together-disabled-people |website=Today |accessdate=24 April 2020 |date=29 November 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Kok |first1=Xing Hui |title=Purple Parade publicises through social media |url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/purple-parade-publicises-through-social-media |website=Today |accessdate=24 April 2020 |date=29 November 2013}}</ref> The first event was eventually held on 30 November 2013.<ref name=\"PP2013\">{{cite web |last1=Sim |first1=Royston |title=Over 4,000 turn up at event to raise awareness about special needs community |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/over-4000-turn-up-at-event-to-raise-awareness-about-special-needs-community |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=24 April 2020 |date=1 December 2013}}</ref>\n\nThe colour purple symbolises royalty, with the square logo representing a call for equality for those with special needs in all areas of society.<ref name=\"PP2013\"/>\n\nSince then, a total of seven Purple Parade events have been held in Singapore, occurring annually on Saturdays in October or November.\n\n==Events==\nEach event took place on a Saturday. It was held at Speakers' Corner in Hong Lim Park from 2013 to 2015, and at the Fountain of Wealth in Suntec City from 2016 to 2019.\n\n===The Purple Parade 2013===\nThe Purple Parade 2013 was held on 30 November 2013. Despite rainy weather, the event attracted a turnout of 4,000 people and pledges that formed a large square at Hong Lim Park. A carnival was organised as part of the event to showcase talents of those with special needs, as well as several performances that were held too. The success of this event prompted organisers to make the event a yearly affair, with more initiatives to support the community.<ref name=\"PP2013\"/>\n\n===The Purple Parade 2014===\n\n===The Purple Parade 2015===\n\n===The Purple Parade 2016===\n\n===The Purple Parade 2017===\n\n===The Purple Parade 2018===\n\n===The Purple Parade 2019===\n\n==Impact==\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of disability organisations in Singapore]]\n* [[List of social service agencies in Singapore]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.purpleparade.sg The Purple Parade]\n\n[[Category:2013 establishments in Singapore]]\n[[Category:Disability in Singapore]]\n[[Category:Disability organisations based in Singapore]]\n[[Category:Human rights in Singapore]]\n[[Category:Recurring events established in 2013]]\n", "name_user": "TheGreatSG'rean", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Purple_Parade"}
